## 💻 Frontend Applications

### 👤 Customer Web App (React + Vite)
*   **Focus:** Clean, fast browsing experience.
*   **Key Pages:**
    *   [Home.jsx](file:///d:/GitHub/efoods-online-food-ordering-and-delivery-management-system/eFoods-frontend/efood-user-frontend/src/pages/Home.jsx) (Hero search)
    *   [RestaurantDetails.jsx](file:///d:/GitHub/efoods-online-food-ordering-and-delivery-management-system/eFoods-frontend/efood-user-frontend/src/pages/RestaurantDetails.jsx) (Menu + Cart)
    *   [Checkout.jsx](file:///d:/GitHub/efoods-online-food-ordering-and-delivery-management-system/eFoods-frontend/efood-user-frontend/src/pages/Checkout.jsx) (Payment integration)
    *   [Profile.jsx](file:///d:/GitHub/efoods-online-food-ordering-and-delivery-management-system/eFoods-frontend/efood-user-frontend/src/pages/Profile.jsx) (Order history)

### 🚗 Driver Web App (React + Vite)
*   **Focus:** Utility and clear navigation.
*   **Key Pages:**
    *   `AvailableJobs.jsx` (List of nearby orders)
    *   `DeliveryMap.jsx` (Google Maps directions)
    *   `Earnings.jsx` (How much they made today)

---

## 🛠️ Implementation Phases

1.  **Phase 1 — Data Isolation:** Create 6 separate databases in MongoDB Atlas.
2.  **Phase 2 — Core Services:** Build Restaurant and Order services first.
3.  **Phase 3 — The Frontends:** Connect the Customer app to the core services.
4.  **Phase 4 — Logic & Support:** Add Delivery, Payments, and then the minor services (Reviews/Loyalty).
5.  **Phase 5 — Dockerization:** Wrap each folder in a `Dockerfile` for easy deployment.
